theorem interior_inter_open_right {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (hB : IsOpen (B : Set X)) :
    interior ((A ∩ B) : Set X) = interior A ∩ B := by
  -- We prove mutual inclusion.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `⊆` direction.
    intro x hx
    -- Membership in `interior (A ∩ B)` gives membership in `A ∩ B`.
    have hxAB : x ∈ (A ∩ B : Set X) := interior_subset hx
    -- Monotonicity of `interior` yields membership in `interior A`.
    have hxA : x ∈ interior (A : Set X) :=
      (interior_mono (Set.inter_subset_left : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ A)) hx
    -- Combine the two pieces of information.
    exact And.intro hxA hxAB.2
  · -- `⊇` direction.
    rintro ⟨hxA_int, hxB⟩
    -- From `x ∈ interior A`, obtain an open neighbourhood `U ⊆ A`.
    rcases mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds.1 hxA_int with ⟨U, hUopen, hxU, hUsubA⟩
    -- Intersect this neighbourhood with `B`, which is open.
    have hOpenInter : IsOpen (U ∩ B : Set X) := hUopen.inter hB
    have hxUInterB : x ∈ (U ∩ B : Set X) := And.intro hxU hxB
    -- The intersection is contained in `A ∩ B`.
    have hSub : (U ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ (A ∩ B : Set X) := by
      intro y hy
      exact And.intro (hUsubA hy.1) hy.2
    -- Hence `x` lies in the interior of `A ∩ B`.
    exact mem_interior_iff_mem_nhds.2 ⟨U ∩ B, hOpenInter, hxUInterB, hSub⟩

theorem closure_interior_eq_empty_iff {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    closure (interior (A : Set X)) = (∅ : Set X) ↔ interior A = ∅ := by
  constructor
  · intro h
    have hSub : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ (∅ : Set X) := by
      have : interior (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := subset_closure
      simpa [h] using this
    exact Set.Subset.antisymm hSub (Set.empty_subset _)
  · intro h
    simpa [h, closure_empty]
